1 Titl e 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes, shall be deposited into the
2 Medical Marijuana Tax Fund created in Section 3 of this act.
3 C. Pursuant to Section 255.2 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma
4 Statutes, the Oklahoma Tax Commission shall have authority to
5 assess, collect and enforce the tax specified in subsection A of
6 this section including any interest and penalty thereon.
7 D. For fiscal year 2022, proceeds from the levy authorized by
8 subsection A of this section shall be apportioned as follows:
9 1. The first Sixty-five Million Dollars ($65,000,000.00) shall
10 be apportioned as follows:
11 a. fifty-nine and twenty-three hundredths percent
12 (59.23%) to the State Public Common School Building
13 Equalization Fund,
14 b. thirty-four and sixty-two hundredths percent (34.62%)
15 to the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority, a
16 division within the State Department of Health, and
17 c. six and fifteen hundredths percent (6.15%) to the
18 State Department of Health and earmarked for drug and
19 alcohol rehabilitation; and
20 2. Any surplus collections shall be apportioned to the General
21 Revenue Fund of the State Treasury.
22 E. If any medical marijuana business licensee intentionally
23 does not remit the taxes as required by the provisions of this
24 section or the provisions of Section 1354 of Title 68 of the
